WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.000
♪ Who's gonna help when the danger overwhelms ♪

00:03.000 --> 00:05.000
♪ And the mysteries are piled high? ♪

00:05.000 --> 00:07.000
♪ Who's gonna be around, never gonna let you down ♪

00:07.000 --> 00:09.000
♪ When you're on a wild ride? ♪

00:09.000 --> 00:11.000
♪ Your friends are always by your side ♪

00:11.000 --> 00:15.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek, he's gonna save the day ♪

00:15.000 --> 00:19.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek, he's gonna save the day ♪

00:19.000 --> 00:21.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek ♪

00:30.000 --> 00:31.000
[ Gasps ]

00:31.000 --> 00:32.000
[ Video game fanfare ]

00:32.000 --> 00:34.000
Treasure.

00:34.000 --> 00:35.000
[ Indistinct conversations ]

00:35.000 --> 00:36.000
Ooh.

00:36.000 --> 00:38.000
[ Video game fanfare playing ]

00:38.000 --> 00:39.000
Treasure!

00:39.000 --> 00:40.000
Treasure!

00:40.000 --> 00:41.000
Treasure?

00:41.000 --> 00:43.000
Treasure!

00:44.000 --> 00:45.000
Hmm.

00:45.000 --> 00:46.000
Treasure.

00:46.000 --> 00:48.000
[ Video game fanfare ]

00:49.000 --> 00:51.000
Craig, baby, have you seen my scarf?

00:51.000 --> 00:53.000
Yeah. Uh, I don't remember where, though.

00:53.000 --> 00:55.000
Ooh, scarf. That's a good idea.

00:55.000 --> 00:57.000
[ Door opens ] No, wait, Mom! Stop!

00:57.000 --> 00:58.000
Oh!

00:58.000 --> 00:59.000
[ Crash! ]

00:59.000 --> 01:01.000
What is all this?

01:01.000 --> 01:03.000
They're my treasures.

01:03.000 --> 01:06.000
I keep them in case I need one of these.

01:06.000 --> 01:09.000
Craig, you cannot be keeping all of this in here.

01:09.000 --> 01:12.000
But Granddad's got a workshop full of stuff like this

01:12.000 --> 01:13.000
that he uses all the time.

01:13.000 --> 01:17.000
Granddad filled that workshop over the course of 70 years.

01:17.000 --> 01:19.000
You filled your closet in nine.

01:19.000 --> 01:21.000
I do an exercise with kids at school

01:21.000 --> 01:23.000
who have too much clutter.

01:23.000 --> 01:25.000
I look at everything they have and ask them,

01:25.000 --> 01:28.000
"Is this something you want, or is this something you need?"

01:28.000 --> 01:29.000
I need it.

01:29.000 --> 01:31.000
You need this cup?

01:31.000 --> 01:33.000
Oh, yeah. You never know when you'll need to pretend

01:34.000 --> 01:35.000
to drink something or what-have-you.

01:35.000 --> 01:38.000
How about this lip balm that I pray you didn't find

01:38.000 --> 01:39.000
in the trash can?

01:39.000 --> 01:41.000
Sewer grate, actually. And I need it.

01:41.000 --> 01:43.000
You can't get rid of any of this?

01:43.000 --> 01:46.000
Not even this action figure you left in the sun?

01:46.000 --> 01:48.000
Melty Man's been through a lot,

01:48.000 --> 01:50.000
and I need him just as much as he needs me.

01:50.000 --> 01:53.000
Craig, I'm throwing away all of this stuff

01:53.000 --> 01:55.000
unless you get it out of this closet.

01:55.000 --> 01:56.000
Wait! W-Wait!

01:57.000 --> 01:58.000
Look, it's going in here. See?

01:58.000 --> 02:01.000
Sweetie, if you get rid of some things,

02:01.000 --> 02:04.000
I think you'll find there's a freedom to feeling lighter.

02:04.000 --> 02:05.000
Naw. I feel great.

02:05.000 --> 02:08.000
[ Grunts ] Thanks, Mom.

02:08.000 --> 02:09.000
Why is this wet?

02:10.000 --> 02:13.000
[ Grunting ]

02:13.000 --> 02:15.000
Hey, guys. What's...up?

02:15.000 --> 02:17.000
[ Whoosh! ]

02:17.000 --> 02:18.000
[ Grunts ] What happened?

02:19.000 --> 02:21.000
We kind of broke the chair lift.

02:21.000 --> 02:23.000
What? But -- But that's how

02:23.000 --> 02:24.000
we get in and out of the stump.

02:24.000 --> 02:26.000
How are we supposed to get down there now?

02:26.000 --> 02:28.000
Uh, we can fall down there?

02:28.000 --> 02:30.000
But how would we get out?

02:30.000 --> 02:33.000
Look, man, I don't have all the answers!

02:33.000 --> 02:34.000
How did this even happen?

02:34.000 --> 02:37.000
Well, I was trying to cut a rock in half with my sword,

02:37.000 --> 02:39.000
and I kind of hit it into the chair lift.

02:39.000 --> 02:41.000
Almost broke that rock, though.

02:41.000 --> 02:43.000
You got anything in there that can fix it?

02:43.000 --> 02:45.000
This is full of very valuable stuff.

02:45.000 --> 02:47.000
But -- But not a wheel.

02:47.000 --> 02:50.000
I think we need to visit the 10 Speeds.

02:51.000 --> 02:54.000
Together: [ Chanting ] Do it. Do it. Do it.

02:55.000 --> 02:57.000
Do it. Do it.

02:57.000 --> 02:59.000
♪♪

02:59.000 --> 03:00.000
[ Shouts ]

03:00.000 --> 03:01.000
Oh, ye-yeah!

03:01.000 --> 03:02.000
Craig: Hey, guys.

03:02.000 --> 03:04.000
♪♪

03:04.000 --> 03:06.000
Yo.

03:06.000 --> 03:08.000
Aw, man. They're doing cool poses.

03:08.000 --> 03:11.000
Uh, what's up, Handlebarb?

03:12.000 --> 03:13.000
You know, the usual.

03:13.000 --> 03:15.000
Doing sick jumps and death-defying stunts.

03:15.000 --> 03:18.000
Well, except for me. [ Sighs ] I got a flat.

03:18.000 --> 03:21.000
I think I rode a hundred miles an hour on it or something.

03:22.000 --> 03:23.000
Or maybe it was that stick.

03:23.000 --> 03:26.000
Yeah. We have a busted wheel ourselves.

03:26.000 --> 03:28.000
Know where we can get a new one?

03:28.000 --> 03:31.000
Hmm, the yard sales have been pretty picked over lately.

03:31.000 --> 03:34.000
There's another place we go to sometimes --

03:34.000 --> 03:35.000
the junkpile.

03:35.000 --> 03:38.000
Only problem is, it's pretty deep in the Creek.

03:38.000 --> 03:40.000
How deep?

03:40.000 --> 03:42.000
Past the Duck Mart.

03:42.000 --> 03:43.000
Duck Mart's not that far.

03:43.000 --> 03:47.000
Not that Duck Mart. The other Duck Mart.

03:47.000 --> 03:50.000
But that's, like, 30 backyards past Tony Mozafari's house!

03:51.000 --> 03:52.000
We could travel by air,

03:52.000 --> 03:54.000
but Mortimer could only carry two of us.

03:54.000 --> 03:58.000
If I fix your flat tire, would you give us a ride?

03:58.000 --> 04:01.000
You could try, but without a patch kit, pfft.

04:01.000 --> 04:03.000
You know, pfft.

04:03.000 --> 04:04.000
Hmm.

04:04.000 --> 04:06.000
[ Video game music ]

04:06.000 --> 04:10.000
♪♪

04:10.000 --> 04:13.000
♪♪

04:13.000 --> 04:17.000
♪♪

04:17.000 --> 04:18.000
There. Fixed.

04:18.000 --> 04:20.000
Huh? Wow. You did it.

04:20.000 --> 04:24.000
10 Speeds, we're going to the junkpile!

04:24.000 --> 04:27.000
Wait. Just because he solved the problem first

04:27.000 --> 04:28.000
means we got to help him?

04:28.000 --> 04:32.000
Hey! We are the 10 Speeds.

04:32.000 --> 04:36.000
Do we leave skidmarks or do we burn rubber?!

04:36.000 --> 04:37.000
Together: Burn rubber.

04:37.000 --> 04:40.000
To the junkpile!

04:40.000 --> 04:42.000
[ Rock music plays ]

04:42.000 --> 04:44.000
♪♪

04:44.000 --> 04:47.000
You're a little safety boy, aren't you?

04:48.000 --> 04:51.000
Wow. You're a lot heavier than you like.

04:51.000 --> 04:54.000
Uh, it's mostly muscle.

04:54.000 --> 04:56.000
Onward!

04:56.000 --> 04:59.000
♪♪

04:59.000 --> 05:03.000
♪♪

05:03.000 --> 05:05.000
Help. Someone help me.

05:05.000 --> 05:08.000
I've been stuck up here for hours.

05:08.000 --> 05:09.000
How'd you get up there?

05:09.000 --> 05:11.000
I don't want to say.

05:11.000 --> 05:13.000
Were you tryin' to kiss a squirrel?

05:13.000 --> 05:14.000
What? No!

05:14.000 --> 05:16.000
I mean, wait, ye -- no!

05:16.000 --> 05:18.000
You got to get me out of here.

05:18.000 --> 05:20.000
I say we leave him.

05:20.000 --> 05:22.000
We need to get that wheel before dinner.

05:22.000 --> 05:23.000
He sealed his own fate.

05:23.000 --> 05:25.000
She's right. We should get going.

05:25.000 --> 05:27.000
It's not our fault his head is that big.

05:27.000 --> 05:29.000
Wait. I think I have an idea.

05:29.000 --> 05:31.000
[ Video game music plays ]

05:31.000 --> 05:33.000
What are you doing?

05:33.000 --> 05:36.000
♪♪

05:36.000 --> 05:38.000
No, wait! Wait! There's a hair! Hair!

05:38.000 --> 05:40.000
[ Screams ]

05:45.000 --> 05:46.000
[ Blows ]

05:46.000 --> 05:48.000
[ Sneezes ]

05:49.000 --> 05:51.000
I gotcha, I gotcha. [ Groans ]

05:51.000 --> 05:54.000
Don't worry. You'll kiss that squirrel someday.

05:54.000 --> 05:56.000
That's not what I was going to do to him.

05:56.000 --> 05:58.000
Thank you so much for saving me.

05:58.000 --> 06:00.000
Here -- I want you to have this.

06:00.000 --> 06:02.000
[ Video game fanfare ] Acorns.

06:02.000 --> 06:05.000
[ Grunts ]

06:06.000 --> 06:07.000
There.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.000
I told my mom this stuff wasn't junk,

06:09.000 --> 06:10.000
and I was right.

06:10.000 --> 06:13.000
Hey, kid. Sorry I wanted to leave you in that tree

06:13.000 --> 06:15.000
for the rest of your life.

06:15.000 --> 06:16.000
We're all good here!

06:16.000 --> 06:20.000
[ Crows cawing ]

06:20.000 --> 06:23.000
What happened here?

06:23.000 --> 06:25.000
Whoa.

06:25.000 --> 06:27.000
This is the junkpile?

06:31.000 --> 06:32.000
[ Gasps ]

06:32.000 --> 06:37.000
♪♪

06:37.000 --> 06:39.000
"10 Thieves."

06:39.000 --> 06:40.000
Oh, it's a pun.

06:40.000 --> 06:42.000
A dangerous pun!

06:42.000 --> 06:45.000
[ Screaming ] Sorry, but you're on your own!

06:45.000 --> 06:48.000
Weird. Well, everyone, find a helmet-holder.

06:48.000 --> 06:50.000
Let's get that wheel and get out of here.

06:50.000 --> 06:52.000
[ Crows cawing ]

06:52.000 --> 06:54.000
So much junk.

06:54.000 --> 06:55.000
It's a good thing I got a tetanus shot

06:55.000 --> 06:57.000
'cause I'm just gonna touch everything.

06:57.000 --> 06:59.000
♪♪

06:59.000 --> 07:02.000
There's got to be a wheel around here somewhere.

07:04.000 --> 07:06.000
[ Gasps ]

07:07.000 --> 07:09.000
It's perfect! In you go!

07:09.000 --> 07:11.000
[ Video game music, beeping ]

07:11.000 --> 07:13.000
Uh, maybe you should turn it clockwise?

07:13.000 --> 07:15.000
Maybe you should turn it sideways?

07:15.000 --> 07:18.000
Hey! Maybe you should put it back...

07:18.000 --> 07:22.000
[ Grunts ] before I turn you clockwise.

07:23.000 --> 07:24.000
Hi-ya!

07:24.000 --> 07:25.000
[ Clank! ]

07:25.000 --> 07:26.000
[ Gasping ]

07:26.000 --> 07:28.000
He's some sorta metal man!

07:29.000 --> 07:32.000
Never mind! New information has come to light!

07:32.000 --> 07:35.000
Now! What is in your hand?

07:35.000 --> 07:37.000
Uh, uh, a bike wheel?

07:37.000 --> 07:39.000
Were the helmets on spikes not enough

07:39.000 --> 07:40.000
to keep you 10 Thieves away?

07:41.000 --> 07:42.000
What are you talking about?

07:42.000 --> 07:44.000
First, you guys take a wheel.

07:44.000 --> 07:46.000
Then another wheel. Then a handlebar.

07:46.000 --> 07:48.000
Then, for some reason, you take an ice-cream scoop.

07:48.000 --> 07:51.000
Not sure what that was about, but I know you took it!

07:51.000 --> 07:54.000
I'm sorry. We didn't know this was yours,

07:54.000 --> 07:57.000
but now that we do, can we please have the wheel?

07:57.000 --> 08:00.000
No! I need them. I'm building a train.

08:00.000 --> 08:02.000
When I found this place, it was just a pit

08:02.000 --> 08:04.000
with some truck tires in it.

08:04.000 --> 08:06.000
I saw value in this junk when no one else did.

08:06.000 --> 08:09.000
This half-used notebook -- it's my cool, new journal!

08:09.000 --> 08:13.000
And this toaster is great for...storing my journal

08:13.000 --> 08:14.000
with all my most private thoughts.

08:14.000 --> 08:16.000
Forget I told you about it.

08:16.000 --> 08:18.000
We would never betray the sanctity of journals

08:18.000 --> 08:20.000
of which we all have.

08:20.000 --> 08:22.000
Just when I pulled these diamonds from the rough,

08:23.000 --> 08:25.000
that's when suddenly everyone wants them again.

08:25.000 --> 08:26.000
But no more!

08:26.000 --> 08:29.000
It's time for you to pay me back,

08:29.000 --> 08:32.000
starting with whatever's in that.

08:32.000 --> 08:33.000
Run!

08:34.000 --> 08:40.000
♪♪

08:40.000 --> 08:42.000
Throw acorns!

08:42.000 --> 08:45.000
Things are about to get nuts.

08:46.000 --> 08:47.000
[ Screams ] They're useless!

08:48.000 --> 08:50.000
[ Panting ] Aah!

08:52.000 --> 08:54.000
Ah-ha! Ow.

08:54.000 --> 08:57.000
♪♪

08:57.000 --> 08:59.000
Where'd he go?

08:59.000 --> 09:02.000
Ha!

09:02.000 --> 09:03.000
Whoa.

09:03.000 --> 09:06.000
Aaaah!

09:06.000 --> 09:08.000
Don't move or we'll --

09:08.000 --> 09:09.000
[ Shouts ]

09:09.000 --> 09:12.000
We got to lose some weight. Get rid of the wheel.

09:12.000 --> 09:15.000
I can't! I've already had so much taken from me.

09:15.000 --> 09:19.000
If I give up some things, will you give up some things, also?

09:20.000 --> 09:21.000
No!

09:21.000 --> 09:24.000
Do I want this or do I need this?

09:24.000 --> 09:27.000
I want this.

09:27.000 --> 09:29.000
[ Groans ] I want this.

09:29.000 --> 09:31.000
[ Groans ] I want this!

09:31.000 --> 09:32.000
I really want this!

09:32.000 --> 09:34.000
But that's a perfectly good Melty Man!

09:35.000 --> 09:37.000
And we're perfectly good boys with lives to lead.

09:38.000 --> 09:40.000
[ Inspirational music plays ]

09:40.000 --> 09:46.000
♪♪

09:46.000 --> 09:49.000
Go, go, go!

09:52.000 --> 09:54.000
[ Groans ] That was really brave of you.

09:54.000 --> 09:55.000
Diving off the boat?

09:56.000 --> 09:58.000
No. Getting rid of all your stuff.

09:58.000 --> 09:59.000
I wouldn't do that.

09:59.000 --> 10:01.000
You never know when you have to move,

10:01.000 --> 10:04.000
and your mom says you can only take one backpack full of stuff.

10:04.000 --> 10:05.000
Did that happen to you?

10:05.000 --> 10:07.000
Well, it was one backpack and three suitcases,

10:07.000 --> 10:11.000
but still...take the wheel and anything else you need.

10:11.000 --> 10:14.000
-[ Shouts ] -Give us back our buddy,

10:14.000 --> 10:15.000
you fake robot!

10:15.000 --> 10:16.000
Whoa! It's cool.

10:16.000 --> 10:18.000
He said we can take whatever.

10:18.000 --> 10:19.000
Both: Really?

10:19.000 --> 10:22.000
Caaaan I take this shield then?

10:22.000 --> 10:24.000
-Fine. -Can I take these dominoes?

10:24.000 --> 10:25.000
No! I need those.

10:25.000 --> 10:26.000
Oh, man. [ Dominoes clatter ]

10:26.000 --> 10:29.000
[ Sighs ] 'kay. Well, then, one domino.

10:29.000 --> 10:32.000
I will make it count.

10:32.000 --> 10:38.000
♪♪

10:38.000 --> 10:40.000
[ Door opens ] -Welcome home, honey.

10:40.000 --> 10:42.000
So, you were right.

10:42.000 --> 10:46.000
I evaluated my treasures and kept only the things I needed.

10:46.000 --> 10:47.000
And what wasn't rotten.

10:47.000 --> 10:49.000
Hey, my scarf.

10:49.000 --> 10:51.000
Of course, I just ordered another one,

10:51.000 --> 10:53.000
so I guess I don't need it anymore.

10:53.000 --> 10:57.000
Do I mind if I hold onto it? I think I can use it.

10:57.000 --> 10:59.000
[ Video game fanfare ]

10:59.000 --> 11:02.000
It does look good.

11:02.000 --> 11:05.000
♪ When it's time to go to bed ♪

11:05.000 --> 11:09.000
♪ Know you don't have to feel alone ♪

11:09.000 --> 11:12.000
♪ 'Cause I'll see you tomorrow ♪

11:13.000 --> 11:14.000
♪ At the creek ♪

11:14.000 --> 11:16.000
Just like I drew it.
